---
import BlogArticleShell from '../../../components/BlogArticleShell.astro';

export const prerender = true;

const canonicalPath = '/blog/mulebuy-taobao';
const publishedISO = '2026-05-03';
---

<BlogArticleShell
  title="Taobao variant grids before Mulebuy paste | mulebuyai.com"
  description="Lock colour/size matrices on Taobao/Tmall-class listings so Spreadsheet curiosity converts into matching warehouse pulls."
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  headline="Taobao detail pages: locking variants before paste"
  publishedISO={publishedISO}
  displayDate="3 May 2026"
>
  <p class="blog-lede" slot="lede">
    Taobao listings expose dense selector grids—easy to screenshot, painful when agents purchase the wrong intersect. Spreadsheet rows rarely encode every permutation; <strong>your Mulebuy intake must mirror the literal matrix you inspected</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>Stable URL hygiene</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Favour item-detail permalinks over shop-wide searches.</li>
    <li>Avoid translator wrappers that strip SKUs.</li>
    <li>Reload after toggling variants to confirm persistence.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Hidden bundles & multi-piece SKUs</h2>
  <p>
    Some listings nest socks, charms, or secondary garments inside one SKU card. Note accessory clauses before approving domestic spend—they inflate QC complexity downstream.
  </p>
</BlogArticleShell>
